BAFANA Bafana star Percy Tau is back in the country. Tau who is plying his trade in the Premier League  side Brighton & Hove Albion completed his first season overseas last Sunday. On Wednesday the 27-year-old collected a snazzy set of wheels (Hyundai i30 N) worth around R700 000 from Hyundai as a brand ambassador of the vehicle manufacturer. Tau will spend sometime with family before joining Bafana camp on 7 June as the national team will be preparing for a friendly match against Uganda. 